FoxPro 2.5 for DOS

PROBLEM: FoxPro doesn't offer a function for typing a centered string in
a @SAY statement.

SOLUTION: Create a "Center" UDF and add it to your procedure file.

function center
parameters Column
column=(80-len(thestring))/2 return column

To use CENTER(), simply type @ROW,CENTER() SAY THESTRING. For example,

THESTRING="Main Menu"
@5,CENTER() SAY THESTRING

And that's all it takes.

